mes be like to be a level 60 cleric with no rez stick:<br>
1) Joined a FG raid to camp Ragefire and 4 other clerics went there also. I logged back on later from what I thought was a safe spot and was immediately attacked by a FG. I gated out. It requires a monk-type though one epic-winner told me he had never seen so many monks at one spot. I felt frustrated.<br>
2) Tried to help two players who had fallen down the well in Icewell Keep. They were relatively close by in a bad spot. I took 20 minutes away from what I was doing but couldn't rescue them. I felt guilty by not helping.<br>
3) Joined a POG raid and was inspected by a player just before zoning-in. I said &quot; Excuse me&quot;. The player said &quot;too late, I'm inspecting you&quot;. I said you're welcome to if you ask. He said don't need to, why am I so paranoid? He kept on about the subject, then had 2 other players, including the raid leader inspect me. I moved away each time. Then he ranted some more on me about why I had said &quot; excuse me&quot; to him and not the others, and how it had him upset. He said, &quot; It's not like I'm inspecting your titties&quot;. I told the raid leader I was leaving, and did. That's my sole player on ignore. I felt upset.<br>
4) As I was working on skills,I was asked to rez a guy and we agreed on 75 pp for the rez and 2 CHs. I CHd the person who asked me and medded while the corpse was shopping for 2 minutes in his bind point. A minute later the corpse and the player were gone. I said &quot; Where are you?&quot; He said , a guildie was rezzing the body. I said thanks for telling me, don't ask again. He said your reputation is justified. I felt cheated and insulted.<br>
<br>
      I do have lots of faults but try to help when I can. If I'm a zone or two away, I often won't go if busy. I don't hide under anonymous. I try to be polite and ask before doing something. I don't inspect without asking, but that's just me. If It's not a raid situation I expect a donation or a set price for a rez. I often ask people whose corpse I come across from traveling if they need a rez, then do it gratis. My mindset is when people make an agreement, I hold them and myself to it.<br>
<br>
 You've seen the ugly of me and them. I'm not sure what your opinion is, but I thought I would share these stories as unvarnished reflections of a few recent events. I apologize to those whose feelings I've inadvertantly hurt, and wish no lasting ill-will to those who are rude to me.<br>
     Kaysha  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukrungleeisenguss.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krungle Eisenguss</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 239<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/14/01 11:50:37 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/krungle101/krunglepic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.brellserilis.net/images/posticons/beertr.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Four Kaysha Quickies</span><hr size=1> Unfortunatly alot of the players think that Clerics owe them Rezzes, Druids owe them SoWs &amp; ports, Wizzies owe them ports, Enchanters owe them crack, and the list goes on. Why? Because you can. That you are busy with something else is of no concern to them...it is your &quot;job&quot;, they say.<br>
<br>
The fact is, if you are not grouped with someone or part of a raid (both people), no one &quot;owes&quot; anyone squat. As a tank I am almost always bound near a bank. I will make a withdraw if I need to do a CR and offer a donation for a SoW, Port, or Rez if the person doing such is not a personal friend or Guildy or Raid/Group member. I will also give an AC &amp;/or HP buff after the donation is accepted or rejected.<br>
<br>
If I am bound at a good distance from my corpse I will do a /who all cleric and try to find one near where I died. If I get the response of &quot;sorry I am busy&quot; or &quot;sorry I am in a group&quot; I move on to someone else, all the while running to recover my corpse with out a rez. If a guildy cleric is near my corpse, I always ask first if they are busy. I realise that Guildies will go out of their way for a guild-mate but I do not want anyone to leave an Exp Group on my acct.<br>
<br>
Maybe I am just unique, but my attitude is no one owes me squat outside of a group/raid situation. If I get myself into a mess it is up to me to get myself out of it. Part of that, sometimes, is finding someone that is able <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  and willing </i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to aide me in accomplishing that end. A few Plat is only fair compensation and aides in increasing the &quot;willing meter&quot;. There has been a couple of times I was in such a pickle I had to wait until some of my friends logged on to form a rescue party. No biggy.<br>
<br>
On the flip side of the coin, there are times I will buff entire parties of younger players and sometimes even power level them. Don't ask me for these things, for I hate beggers. Offer me a donation for it and I will reject it. Some times I do it as a way to get a drop for a quest. I try to stay for a bit after I get my drop. I feel that that is fair compensation in a &quot;you scratch my back, I will scratch yours&quot; kinda way. Sometimes I am just too busy to do it, tho, or LoM, or heading into a zone that I might need the mana for self heals &amp;/or Crowd control (like Nek). <br>
<br>
Don't let nimrods get you down. Enjoy the game. Help others when you can. Don't worry about it when you can't. And, above all, do not take any BS from beggers. <p><center><img src="http://members.aol.com/krungle101/krunglesig.jpg" border=0></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uquemnwyndrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quemn Wyndrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Assist Dammit!</span><br>  Posts: 1044<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/14/01 12:14:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Four Kaysha Quickies</span><hr size=1> aww, i've always thought you were a good cleric Kaysha <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><a href=http://www.geocities.com/quemnthebard><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~qthebard/blur.jpg border=0></a></center>
